Rating: 4
Made this for the first time tonight, but, as usual, I modified it to simplify it. Only had about 1-3/4 lbs. of bone-in chicken breasts that I skinned and de-fatted (as much as possible). Placed the breasts in a small casserole dish. Then I sauteed 1 head of garlic cloves (peeled and smashed) in a little olive oil until nicely browned. Added 3/4 cup of wine, a bay leaf, and 1/4 tsp. dried thyme, and brought the mixture to a boil. Poured it over the breasts in the casserole dish and baked the whole thing about 40 minutes, covered, at 400 degrees (turned the chicken over once during the baking time). This was SO simple, and it omitted standing over the chicken to change it from top to bottom in the pot every 5 minutes. It was DELICIOUS, even though it didn't look like the picture, but who cares??? The juice that is leftover is wonderful, and I can't wait to use it as broth in another recipe. Served this with leftover "Mashed Potatoes with Green Onions and Parmesan" (on this site) and a 10 oz. box of very unimaginative Green Giant Teriyaki Vegetables. It was a meal TO DIE FOR, and SUPER SIMPLE!!!

