To the cook from Studio City; A good rule of thumb is to use a similar wine (but of lower pedigree) for cooking a dish than for accompanying the dish. For example, if you would serve a white burgundy with this dish, you would use a white burgundy to cook with. You could also use a closely similar wine but this can be a bit confusing unless your wine background is substantial. By sticking with using the same varietal and viticultural area, you are pretty well assured that the flavors and style will be complementary.

