I made it today substituting virgin rapeseed oil for virgin olive oil, which does not stand the cooking temperature. There is no idea in wasting virgin olive oil, which loses its aroma at high temperatures - virgin olive oil should only be used in salads and other cold dishes. Virgin rapeseed oil, on the contrary, stands well the high temperature and gives an interesting nutty aroma to the dish. I have eaten enough of chaffy oatmeal porridge in my childhood, so I peeled the garlic. I happened to have an extra half of a lemon and added it to the casserole, and also thickened the sauce with cornstarch. I used cheap Italian white wine (Soave) and do not recommend aromatic grape varieties such as Sauvignon Blanc for this kind of cooking.

